Perfect! Here's your **Assignment 5 Beginner-Friendly Workflow** for creating **CloudWatch Alarms** ‚Äì one for **billing** and another for **CPU utilization**, with **SNS notification**.

---

## ‚úÖ Assignment 5: CloudWatch Alarms for Billing and EC2 CPU ‚Äì Beginner-Friendly Workflow

### üéØ Objective:

1. Create a **billing alarm** that triggers if estimated charges go above **\$500**.
2. Create a **CPU utilization alarm** for an EC2 instance that:

   * Triggers if CPU > **65%**
   * Sends a notification using **SNS topic**

---

## üß© Step-by-Step Lab Instructions

---

## üîπ Part 1: Billing Alarm

### 1. **Enable Billing Metrics**

> üö® Billing alarms work **only in the us-east-1 (N. Virginia)** region!

* Go to: [https://console.aws.amazon.com/billing/home](https://console.aws.amazon.com/billing/home)
* Click on **‚ÄúBilling Preferences‚Äù**
* Enable:

  * ‚úÖ Receive Billing Alerts
* Save changes

---

### 2. **Create Billing Alarm**

* Go to: [https://console.aws.amazon.com/cloudwatch/](https://console.aws.amazon.com/cloudwatch/)
* Region: Select **N. Virginia (us-east-1)** from top-right
* Click **Alarms** ‚Üí **Create Alarm**
* Choose metric ‚Üí Search: `Billing` ‚Üí Select `Total Estimated Charge`
* Click on metric: `EstimatedCharges`
* Select `Currency` = USD ‚Üí Click **Select metric**

#### Set threshold:

* Whenever estimated charges **Greater than** `500`
* Period: `6 hours` (or keep default)
* Click **Next**

---

### 3. **Notification (Optional for billing)**

You can skip SNS for now or create a topic (see next section).

* Click **Next** ‚Üí Name: `Billing-Alarm-Over500`
* Click **Create alarm**

---

## üîπ Part 2: CPU Utilization Alarm with SNS Notification

### 1. **Create SNS Topic**

* Go to: [https://console.aws.amazon.com/sns/v3](https://console.aws.amazon.com/sns/v3/home)
* Click **Topics** ‚Üí **Create topic**
* Type: Standard
* Name: `CPUAlarmNotifyTopic`
* Click **Create topic**

### 2. **Create Subscription**

* Click your new topic ‚Üí **Create subscription**
* Protocol: `Email`
* Endpoint: Enter your email ID
* Click **Create subscription**
* üì® Go to your email and **Confirm** the subscription!

---

### 3. **Create EC2 CPU Alarm**

* CloudWatch ‚Üí Alarms ‚Üí **Create Alarm**
* Choose metric ‚Üí EC2 ‚Üí Per-instance metrics ‚Üí Select your instance
* Select **CPUUtilization** ‚Üí Click **Select metric**

#### Set threshold:

* Condition: **Greater than 65**
* Period: `5 minutes`
* Click **Next**

#### Notification:

* Select SNS Topic: `CPUAlarmNotifyTopic`

* (If not showing, refresh)

* Click **Next** ‚Üí Name: `EC2-High-CPU-Alarm`

* Click **Create alarm**

---

### ‚úÖ Final Verification:

* In **CloudWatch ‚Üí Alarms**, check both alarms.
* In **SNS ‚Üí Subscriptions**, confirm your email status is `Confirmed`.
* Trigger an alarm by creating load on EC2 or increasing billing.

---

### üß™ Optional Tip:

* Use `stress` command on EC2 instance (Linux) to simulate CPU load:

```bash
sudo yum install stress -y
stress --cpu 4 --timeout 300
```

